<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-52-1012 </DOCNO><TEXT>We present a new approach to SU{sub 2L} {times} U{sub 1} radiative correctionsat high energies. Our approach is based on the infrared summation methodsof Yennie, Frautschi and Suura, taken together with the Weinberg-'t Hooftrenormalization group equation. Specific processes which have been realizedvia explicit Monte Carlo algorithms are e{sup +}e{sup {minus}} {yields}f{bar f}{prime} + n({gamma}), f = {mu}, {tau}, d, s, u, c, b or t ande{sup +}e{sup {minus}} {yields} e{sup +}e{sup {minus}} + n({gamma}),where n({gamma}), denotes multiple photo emission on an event-by-eventbasis. Exemplary Monte Carlo data are presented. 16 refs., 4 figs.</TEXT></DOC>